11. Failure Handling

Scenario| Handling
Invalid syslog payload| Reject and log validation failure
Unknown device| Log unmapped device event
Duplicate event| Deduplicate using event correlation
Syslog service unavailable| Retry event delivery
Event processing failure| Persist failed event for retry

---

12. Scalability Considerations

- High volume syslog events expected
- Event processing should be asynchronous
- Queue-based buffering recommended
- Config Event Processor should support horizontal scaling
- Event persistence should support bulk ingestion

---

13. Security Considerations

- Accept events only from authorized Syslog Service
- Validate event authenticity
- Audit all received configuration events
- Secure inter-service communication

---

14. Assumptions

- Network devices emit syslog messages for configuration changes
- Syslog Service is already deployed in SDN environment
- Device inventory data is available for correlation
- Reliable communication exists between Syslog Service and SDN

